==English==

===Adverb===
'''at a [[loss]]'''

# Below the [[cost]] or [[price]] of purchase.
#: ''We sold those old computers '''at a loss'''.''
# {{idiom}} Not [[sure]]; [[uncertain]]; [[lacking]] further [[ideas]], [[direction]], or [[ability]].
#: ''I have fixed the parts I understand, and the rest leaves me '''at a loss'''.''

====Usage notes====
*Used with [[for]], as
*:''at a loss for ideas''
*:''at a loss for how to proceed''

